genresAdvancedInfo.name: diy pop punk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A subgenre of punk rock that combines the catchy melodies and upbeat rhythms of pop music with the DIY ethos of punk rock. It's characterized by fast tempos, distorted guitars, and lyrics that often deal with teenage angst and rebellion. DIY pop punk bands often self-produce and self-release their music, and they prioritize fun and energy over technical proficiency.
